*gentoolkit-0.1.1 (2 Feb 2002)

  2 Feb 2002; Leo Lipelis <aeoo@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :

  Jochem Kossen has added a nice diff/sdiff mode to etc-update.  As many
  people do not prefer vim, etc-update will now default to using diff for
  displaying changes and sdiff for merging changes! This means, if you
  use any editor other than vim, the script will now work for you out of
  the box. But, vim users need not panic! Vim diff functionality is
  still there in the script.  Just read the top of the etc-update file
  and configure it appropriately.  To sum up: vim users keep getting
  what they've been getting, and everyone else gets cool diff/sdiff
  mode.

